title: For Sale:  Zastava M70 DMR Build With Scope (Not an N-Pap)
postcontent:
This is a unique AK, it's built from a m70 military kit, and as such it has the elements like the Grenade sights and flip-up night sights (dark and non-functional). Built on an NDS-5 reciever with a buldged trunnion. I believe the finish is parkerized.

Comes with a LPS 4x6 Tip 2 PSL scope (non-illuminated model) that includes the rubber eyepiece and lens cover. A side rail was added that FITS BOTH AK-Style AND PSL-Style SCOPES! The only real negative about this is that the rivet heads are unfinished, which is an easy fix..

Has custom maple furniture that is slightly oversized for more grip area, I found the handle to be uncomfortable to me so I swapped it out for a standard M70 grip. The stock has a very comfortable raised cheek rest to use with the scope, but makes it a little difficult to use the iron sights.

The muzzle device is also unique, it's a FAL browning-type flash hider that has been welded (very cleanly) to a cut-off muzzle device in the proper 14x1 LH thread. It makes for a very effective flash suppressor, plus it looks great by giving the rifle a very DMR look.

The rifle has recently been looked over and checked by Texas Shooter Supply in Spring, TX to ensure it is safe and functional. They even removed the previously modded trigger group and added an improved Tapco G2 that they did themselves, the gun has a very light and quick break, fully single stage.

I am the second owner, it has a fairly low round count and the barrel is in very good condition with sharp lands and a shiny bore. The barrel is non-chrome lined Yugo Milsurp.
Comes with 3 magazines and a set of milsurp Zastava handguards plus the original matched maple grip. Leather sling.


$1200 OBO.

title: For Sale:  US .30 Caliber, M1917 Rifle Remington
postcontent:
US .30-06 Caliber, M1917 (Enfield) Rifle, made by Remington, Serial No. 388xxx.  Based on this number the manufacture date is somewhere around 7/1918.  However, the barrel is stamped 10/18, so it might actually be closer to that.

This rifle appears to be unaltered and complete, except for a sling and the sling swivels which are missing.  From what I can see, without stripping the gun down, the barrel (5 groove), receiver and parts directly connect to those items are all marked "R" (Remington).  The front portion of the stock and rear swivel mount are marked "E" (Eddystone).  The bolt "celebrates the diversity of the manufacturers" - the bolt handle is marked "W" (Winchester), the rear cap is marked "E" and one other visibly part is marked "R".  

The metal seems to be polished with a certain level of bluing, although is seems rather gray.  There appears to be no serious rust, probably due to its nickel steel.  The proof marks and acceptance stamps are all quite clear.  The stock has a lot of dings, dents, nicks and a couple plugs, but, no cracks.

It doesn't appear that it has gone through an arsenal rebuild program.  If it did it was at least spared the Parkerized sandblast and refinish, except for the rear cap on the bolt.

My son got it from a friends dad with the intention of turning it into a hunting rifle.  I believed he fired a couple shots through it.  

It is hardly perfect, "Good" condition (maybe?), but I hope it's nice enough that someone might want to preserved for its historical value.  It was the predominate US rifle in WW I and most likely the type my Grandfather and his brother carried.

You must have ID / WDL and be eligible under State law to possess a firearm.

I have a Pre Ban Yugoslavian under folder manufactured from 1959-1963 time frame it is Rare and not many were imported with a milled receiver Without the legion Dimples. They did not start milling Legion Dimples into the receivers until the late 1960s till around 1969. Then they started producing the zestava NPap and the OPap models which were Serbian and they were imported around 1972 till current. It comes with factory NS, Bayonet lug, Grenade launcher sites, slant muzzle break, Hogue pistol Grip and cleaning rod, Comes with 8-30rd mags, 2-40rd mags, 1-75rd chinese drum and the mags are Bulgarian steel, Plus about 1200rds of X39 ammo most of it is High end Russian, Brass cased ammo?  This AK bears no import markings or stamps and the receiver is not like any others on the market with a milled receiver.
